  ('jee-chemistry-atomic-structure-q01', 'jee-chemistry-atomic-structure', 'The maximum number of electrons in a shell with principal quantum number n is:', 'n', '2n', '2n²', 'n²', 'C', 'A shell holds at most 2n² electrons.', 0),
  ('jee-chemistry-atomic-structure-q02', 'jee-chemistry-atomic-structure', 'The principle that no two electrons can have all four quantum numbers identical is:', 'Aufbau principle', 'Hund''s rule', 'Pauli exclusion principle', 'Heisenberg principle', 'C', 'The Pauli exclusion principle forbids identical sets of four quantum numbers.', 1),
  ('jee-chemistry-atomic-structure-q03', 'jee-chemistry-atomic-structure', 'The azimuthal quantum number l for a d subshell is:', '0', '2', '3', '1', 'B', 'For d orbitals, l = 2 (s = 0, p = 1, d = 2, f = 3).', 2),
  ('jee-chemistry-atomic-structure-q04', 'jee-chemistry-atomic-structure', 'The Balmer series of hydrogen corresponds to electron transitions ending at:', 'n = 1', 'n = 4', 'n = 2', 'n = 3', 'C', 'Balmer lines arise from transitions down to n = 2 and lie in the visible region.', 3),
  ('jee-chemistry-atomic-structure-q05', 'jee-chemistry-atomic-structure', 'Hund''s rule of maximum multiplicity states that electrons:', 'Always pair with opposite spin', 'Pair up first', 'Occupy the highest orbital', 'Fill orbitals singly before pairing', 'D', 'Degenerate orbitals are singly filled before any pairing occurs.', 4),
  ('jee-chemistry-atomic-structure-q06', 'jee-chemistry-atomic-structure', 'The electronic configuration of chromium (Z = 24) is anomalous as:', '[Ar] 3d4 4s2', '[Ar] 3d6 4s0', '[Ar] 3d5 4s1', '[Ar] 3d3 4s3', 'C', 'Chromium adopts 3d5 4s1 for the extra stability of a half-filled d subshell.', 5),
  ('jee-chemistry-atomic-structure-q07', 'jee-chemistry-atomic-structure', 'Heisenberg''s uncertainty principle relates the uncertainties in:', 'Position and momentum', 'Charge and mass', 'Energy and charge', 'Spin and mass', 'A', 'It states delta x times delta p is at least h/(4 pi).', 6),
  ('jee-chemistry-atomic-structure-q08', 'jee-chemistry-atomic-structure', 'According to the (n + l) rule, which subshell fills first?', '3d', '4s', '4p', '4d', 'B', '4s (n + l = 4) fills before 3d (n + l = 5) under the Aufbau ordering.', 7),
  ('jee-chemistry-periodicity-q01', 'jee-chemistry-periodicity', 'Across a period from left to right, atomic radius generally:', 'Increases', 'Decreases', 'Stays constant', 'First increases then decreases', 'B', 'Rising effective nuclear charge pulls electrons closer, shrinking the radius.', 0),
  ('jee-chemistry-periodicity-q02', 'jee-chemistry-periodicity', 'The modern periodic law arranges elements by increasing:', 'Valency', 'Atomic mass', 'Density', 'Atomic number', 'D', 'Moseley''s modern law orders elements by atomic number.', 1),
  ('jee-chemistry-periodicity-q03', 'jee-chemistry-periodicity', 'Down a group, ionisation energy generally:', 'Decreases', 'Increases', 'Stays constant', 'Becomes zero', 'A', 'Added shells increase size, so electrons are easier to remove going down a group.', 2),
  ('jee-chemistry-periodicity-q04', 'jee-chemistry-periodicity', 'The most electronegative element in the periodic table is:', 'Nitrogen', 'Chlorine', 'Oxygen', 'Fluorine', 'D', 'Fluorine has the highest electronegativity on the Pauling scale.', 3),
  ('jee-chemistry-periodicity-q05', 'jee-chemistry-periodicity', 'Elements of groups 1 and 2 belong to the:', 'p-block', 's-block', 'd-block', 'f-block', 'B', 'Groups 1 and 2 have their last electron in an s orbital, defining the s-block.', 4),
  ('jee-chemistry-periodicity-q06', 'jee-chemistry-periodicity', 'The second ionisation energy of an element compared with the first is always:', 'Smaller', 'Larger', 'Equal', 'Zero', 'B', 'Removing an electron from a cation needs more energy, so IE2 is greater than IE1.', 5),
