  ('jee-chemistry-aldehydes-ketones-acids-q04', 'jee-chemistry-aldehydes-ketones-acids', 'The Cannizzaro reaction occurs with aldehydes that lack a/an:', 'Carbonyl group', 'Double bond', 'Methyl group', 'Alpha-hydrogen', 'D', 'Aldehydes without an alpha-hydrogen undergo the Cannizzaro disproportionation.', 3),
  ('jee-chemistry-aldehydes-ketones-acids-q05', 'jee-chemistry-aldehydes-ketones-acids', 'Which compound is the strongest acid?', 'Trichloroacetic acid', 'Acetic acid', 'Ethanol', 'Phenol', 'A', 'Three electron-withdrawing chlorines make trichloroacetic acid the strongest here.', 4),
  ('jee-chemistry-aldehydes-ketones-acids-q06', 'jee-chemistry-aldehydes-ketones-acids', 'A positive iodoform test indicates the presence of a:', 'Carboxylic acid', 'Simple ether', 'Primary amine', 'Methyl ketone', 'D', 'Methyl ketones (and ethanal) give the yellow iodoform precipitate.', 5),
